21:53.854 --> 21:58.316
It marks the first real
communion between the Hummel
and the Hudson clans.

21:58.401 --> 22:01.319
I imagine that when
the Bouviers and the Kennedys
first broke bread...

22:01.404 --> 22:04.114
there was a similar sense
of joy and urgency.

22:04.198 --> 22:07.784
So let me raise
my Shirley Temple
to our new little family.

22:09.662 --> 22:11.913
- We're not a family.
- Finn.

22:11.998 --> 22:16.501
It's cool. You're right.
Your mom and I are just enjoying
each other's company right now.

22:16.585 --> 22:19.796
Let's just enjoy dinner.
I mean, I'm buyin', right?
[Chuckles]

22:19.880 --> 22:21.423
[Chuckles]

22:21.507 --> 22:23.633
- You playing basketball now?
- Yeah.

22:23.718 --> 22:26.511
- But I actually kinda like football better.
- I didn't know that.

22:26.595 --> 22:30.557
- Sounds crazy, but I miss getting hit.
- Pure boyish insanity.

22:30.641 --> 22:32.892
No, it isn't.
I totally get that.

22:32.977 --> 22:36.479
I used to love the feeling
of getting my clock cleaned
and then popping right up.

22:36.564 --> 22:38.690
- Kinda reminded me of being alive.
- Oh, yeah.

22:38.774 --> 22:41.943
Why hasn't anyone commented on
the new jeans I got Carole?

22:42.069 --> 22:44.738
Oh, come on.
Notice that the waistband falls
well below the belly button.

22:44.864 --> 22:46.906
A welcome change.
[Burt]
Sure, Kurt.

22:46.991 --> 22:50.869
Hey, you know, I sell tires to
one of the assistant coaches
from the Browns.

22:50.953 --> 22:53.413
- I can probably get you
tickets, if you want to go.
- That'd be awesome.

22:53.497 --> 22:56.291
- I've never been to
an N.F.L. game live before.
- Well, no problem.

22:56.375 --> 22:58.376
Wow.

22:58.461 --> 23:02.297
- For a place called Breadstix,
these really suck.
- [Both Laughing]

23:04.133 --> 23:06.384
[Burt]
It's really just
stale bread, isn't it?

23:06.469 --> 23:08.094
[Carole]
Yeah—

23:10.848 --> 23:13.892
- Hey. You finally choose one?
- No. They're all wrong.

23:13.976 --> 23:16.603
Well, they all
look like gray to me.

23:16.687 --> 23:20.106
Maybe if they were different
colored sports uniforms, you'd
work harder to tell them apart.

23:20.191 --> 23:23.860
I knew it. I knew when I
started in on the football with Finn,
you'd take it personal.

23:23.944 --> 23:25.695
How could I not, Dad?

23:25.780 --> 23:28.907
When was the last time
you were that engaged
in a conversation with me?

23:28.991 --> 23:31.326
I'm sorry. I don't know
what you want here.

23:31.410 --> 23:35.080
What I want is for you
to appreciate how hard it is
for me to watch you bond...

23:35.164 --> 23:37.332
with the son that
you've obviously
always wanted.

23:37.416 --> 23:41.628
Oh, suddenly I'm not the guy
who sat through Riverdance
three years in a row?

23:41.712 --> 23:44.923
Look, Kurt, I love you,

23:45.007 --> 23:47.425
and I am sympathetic
to all of your stuff.

23:47.510 --> 23:50.470
But come on, buddy,
we got a deal here, right?

23:50.554 --> 23:54.099
I don't try to change you,
you don't try to change me.

23:54.183 --> 23:59.062
You are my son, and a little
guy talk with some other kid
isn't gonna change that.

24:00.314 --> 24:03.566
Guy talk?
I'm a guy.

24:03.651 --> 24:06.194
Come on.
You know what I mean.

24:07.696 --> 24:10.240
Maybe I was wrong.

24:10.324 --> 24:13.576
Maybe it is too soon
for you to start getting
serious with someone.

24:15.037 --> 24:17.872
Your mom's been dead eight years.
You know that.

24:24.880 --> 24:29.300
Why'd you fix me up with Carole?
Wasn't it to make me happy?
'Cause that's what you told me.

24:29.385 --> 24:32.303
Can you go now?

24:32.388 --> 24:36.099
I'm a half an hour behind
on my moisturizing routine
and I need to get up early.

24:43.232 --> 24:45.900
Do you want half
of my peppermint patty?

24:45.985 --> 24:47.819
No. I don't
put junk in my body.

24:47.903 --> 24:50.989
Why are you doing this?
We like you
no matter how you look.

24:51.073 --> 24:52.991
And those shake diets
are really unhealthy.

24:53.075 --> 24:56.828
They also don't really work.
As soon as you go off them,
you gain back the weight you lost.

24:56.912 --> 24:59.664
You know what?
I don't want to hear it!

24:59.748 --> 25:03.710
You have no idea how much
I'm sacrificing to be a Cheerio,
to look fantastic,

25:03.794 --> 25:05.795
to finally fit in at this school.

25:08.549 --> 25:11.676
We were just trying
to look out for you.

25:11.760 --> 25:13.678
We just want you
to be healthy.

25:13.762 --> 25:16.431
Stop getting all up in my face,
telling me what I can
and cannot do.

25:16.515 --> 25:19.267
And I'm really hungry,
so stop trying
to get me to eat you!

25:19.351 --> 25:22.478
Hold up. Did she just say
she wanted to eat us?

25:23.856 --> 25:27.233
The point is that Fanny Brice
is the most iconic role—

25:27.318 --> 25:29.819
Aw, damn.

25:34.950 --> 25:37.994
- [Hissing]
- Hmm.

25:38.078 --> 25:41.247
Your blood pressure's low.
Maybe that's why you fainted.

25:41.332 --> 25:45.668
Your mom will be here soon.
I'll go and get you
some ginger ale.

25:52.509 --> 25:54.427
Thanks.
I'm not hungry.

25:54.511 --> 25:57.764
Yes, you are.
You're starving.

25:58.682 --> 26:02.227
I know.
I've been there.

26:02.311 --> 26:05.230
Did all the other kids
start looking like food
right before you fainted?

26:05.314 --> 26:07.315
Yeah.
How'd you know?

26:07.399 --> 26:10.360
Been there.

26:10.444 --> 26:12.570
Eat the granola bar.

26:12.655 --> 26:15.073
Why are you being
so nice to me?

26:15.157 --> 26:20.453
I can't remember the last time
you said two words to me
that weren't "you" and "suck."

26:21.664 --> 26:23.998
'Cause I was you-
scared.

26:24.083 --> 26:28.169
Hating myself
for eating a cookie.
But I got over it.

26:28.254 --> 26:31.589
Yeah, of course you did,
Miss Pretty Blonde
With the White Girl Ass.

26:31.674 --> 26:33.967
When you start eating
for somebody else,

26:34.051 --> 26:36.719
so that they can grow
and be healthy,

26:36.804 --> 26:38.846
your relationship
to food changes.

26:38.931 --> 26:44.269
What I realized is that if
I'm so willing to eat right
to take care of this baby,

26:44.353 --> 26:47.355
why am I not willing
to do it for myself?

26:48.023 --> 26:50.608
You are so lucky.

26:50.693 --> 26:53.945
You've always been at home
in your body.

26:54.029 --> 26:56.698
Don't let Ms. Sylvester
take that away from you.

27:00.035 --> 27:02.078
I'm so embarrassed.

27:03.789 --> 27:06.040
This isn't me.

27:07.960 --> 27:11.087
How did I become this person?

27:13.716 --> 27:15.341
You are beautiful.

27:17.636 --> 27:19.220
You know that.

27:22.141 --> 27:25.852
I'm gonna stay here with you
until your mom comes, okay?

27:28.605 --> 27:32.525
[Woman]
♪ Home sweet home ♪
[Chattering, Laughing]

27:32.609 --> 27:35.528
♪ Tonight's the night ♪

27:35.612 --> 27:38.531
I don't think
this is gonna work out.
♪♪ [Continues]

27:38.615 --> 27:41.326
So, I'm thinking about
closing up early.

27:41.410 --> 27:45.246
Want to order a pizza,
maybe snuggle up,
pop in a movie?

27:45.331 --> 27:48.708
I don't think
we should make a habit of
spending the night together.

27:48.792 --> 27:50.668
All we did was sleep.

27:50.753 --> 27:54.130
No. All you did was sleep.
I was up all night
with you kicking me.

27:54.214 --> 27:57.216
Sorry.
Them's the night terrors.

27:57.301 --> 28:00.595
Look, I'm in the middle
of a divorce, and you—

28:00.679 --> 28:05.558
Are you really
where you want to be? I mean,
being somebody's mistress?

28:05.642 --> 28:08.686
Don't you think you deserve
a little bit more than that?

28:08.771 --> 28:12.815
You can be the life of the party
every night and drink
till you can't see straight,

28:12.900 --> 28:18.154
but you're always going
to feel empty inside
until you really find a home.

28:18.238 --> 28:21.783
♪ I'm on my way ♪

28:21.867 --> 28:24.952
- But, listen, if you need
a place to stay tonight-
- No.

28:26.622 --> 28:30.291
You're right. You're right.
I am worth more than that.

28:31.794 --> 28:33.711
Tonight, I'm gonna
go over to Buddy's,

28:33.796 --> 28:35.713
and I'm gonna
tell him we're through.

28:35.798 --> 28:39.175
If he still had the powers of speech,
I'm sure he'd be thankful.

28:39.259 --> 28:42.095
You know, RinkyDinks
loses $8,000 a night.

28:42.179 --> 28:45.390
Turns out, roller rinks-

28:45.474 --> 28:47.809
not so profitable.

28:47.893 --> 28:49.894
[Chuckles]

28:56.902 --> 29:00.321
You always give me
the right advice,
Mr. Schuester.

29:01.573 --> 29:03.574
See you around.
[Clicks]

29:06.954 --> 29:09.288
[Sighs]

29:09.498 --> 29:11.499
[School Bell Rings]

29:11.583 --> 29:15.294
Finn, we need to talk.

29:15.379 --> 29:18.339
We have to break up
our parents immediately.

29:18.424 --> 29:20.258
I screwed up.

29:20.342 --> 29:23.219
I feel like the guy who
set up Liza and David Gest.

29:23.303 --> 29:25.221
It hurt you, didn't it?

29:25.305 --> 29:28.182
When I was talking sports
with your dad and stuff.

29:28.308 --> 29:31.561
I could tell
that you were-
Left out?

29:31.645 --> 29:33.438
Invisible?

29:33.522 --> 29:34.939
Yeah.

29:35.023 --> 29:37.942
I don't like that my mom's
forgetting about my dad.

29:38.026 --> 29:40.820
It's up to me to keep
his memory alive.

29:40.904 --> 29:44.449
And I don't want to
move in with you.
No offense.

29:44.533 --> 29:46.868
None taken.

29:46.952 --> 29:49.370
So we put
an end to them.

29:49.496 --> 29:52.123
Agreed?
Agreed.

29:58.005 --> 29:59.922
What are you doing?

30:00.007 --> 30:03.176
I'm going to
flush Dad's ashes
down the toilet.

30:04.887 --> 30:06.471
Have you lost your mind?

30:06.555 --> 30:09.474
What? I'm just doing
the same thing
you're doing to him.

30:09.558 --> 30:13.019
What's the point of keeping his
remains if you’re just gonna
dump them out like an ashtray?

30:14.730 --> 30:17.148
Fine.

30:18.150 --> 30:20.526
- What are you doing?
- What you want.

30:20.611 --> 30:23.988
What we've been doing
for the last 15 years—
pretending.

30:24.072 --> 30:27.408
Come on, Finn,
let's sit and watch TV
as a family.

30:27.534 --> 30:30.703
[TV: Clicks On]
Look! A basketball game.
Your dad would've liked that.

30:30.787 --> 30:33.122
-What do you think, Christopher?
-Mom, you're being crazy.

30:33.207 --> 30:35.416
And you're being selfish.

30:35.501 --> 30:38.878
I like Burt. I-I-

30:38.962 --> 30:42.048
I haven't felt this way
about a guy since your dad died.

30:42.132 --> 30:44.550
At least not one
who felt it back.

30:44.635 --> 30:46.844
This family works.
I don't want it
to get screwed up!

30:46.929 --> 30:49.847
This family manages.

30:49.932 --> 30:52.141
We get by.

30:52.226 --> 30:55.895
You just don't know any
differently because you think
what we have is normal.

31:04.404 --> 31:07.114
I do this with him
every night.

31:08.825 --> 31:13.329
I take the urn to bed with me,
and I talk to him about my day.

31:14.540 --> 31:17.250
Sixteen years...

31:17.334 --> 31:20.336
I've been asking him
for advice and—

31:21.964 --> 31:23.881
and waiting
to hear his laugh...

31:23.966 --> 31:26.968
and for him to tell me
that he loves me.

31:29.137 --> 31:32.014
And he never does.

31:32.099 --> 31:34.016
And he never will.

31:38.021 --> 31:40.439
I won't do it.
I'm not moving.
I'm not ready.

31:40.524 --> 31:42.650
And he wouldn't want you
to do this if I wasn't ready.

31:42.734 --> 31:45.528
You didn't know him, Finn.

31:49.408 --> 31:53.953
Sweetheart,
I love you so much.

31:56.206 --> 31:58.583
We don't need
any more memories or ghosts.

31:58.667 --> 32:02.628
We need a family, a home.

32:15.767 --> 32:17.810
[Chattering]

32:19.938 --> 32:24.191
Well, with a name like Tracy,
I assumed you were a lady.

32:25.611 --> 32:27.945
Quite a turnout
for a pep rally.

32:28.030 --> 32:30.948
On assembly days,
I arrange for the rest of
the school to be fumigated,

32:31.033 --> 32:34.493
leaving the gymnasium
the only place
with breathable air.

32:34.578 --> 32:37.496
Come on. That was clever.
You might want to start
writing down my little bon mots.

32:37.581 --> 32:39.874
I'm gonna be dropping
some beauties on you.

32:39.958 --> 32:42.877
You know, this is
just a freelance job.

32:42.961 --> 32:45.212
I was short-listed
for the Pulitzer last year...

32:45.297 --> 32:47.590
for my Newsweek piece
on high school athletes
going pro.

32:47.674 --> 32:50.885
So my cover story
isn't a fluff piece?

32:50.969 --> 32:53.054
Nope.
Hard-hitting investigation.

32:53.889 --> 32:56.724
[Cheering]

33:05.150 --> 33:09.195
Feast your ears
on this smokin' intro.

33:11.031 --> 33:12.990
In a few seconds.

33:13.075 --> 33:15.076
So important
to build the tension.

33:20.415 --> 33:22.416
What is she doing?

33:23.460 --> 33:26.045
[Microphone Feedback]
Hey, guys.

33:26.129 --> 33:27.922
I'm Mercedes Jones.

33:29.049 --> 33:31.676
[Exhales]
So most of you know...

33:31.760 --> 33:34.136
Cheerios is about
perfection and winning,

33:34.221 --> 33:37.807
looking hot
and being popular.

33:37.891 --> 33:40.476
Still building the tension.

33:40.560 --> 33:43.354
[Feedback]

33:43.438 --> 33:46.440
Well, I think that it should be
about something different.

33:49.111 --> 33:52.113
How many of you
at this school feel fat?

33:54.991 --> 33:59.578
How many of you feel like maybe
you're not worth very much?

33:59.663 --> 34:03.332
Or you're ugly,
or you have too many pimples
and not enough friends?

34:05.502 --> 34:09.296
Well, I felt
all those things about myself
at one time or another.

34:11.383 --> 34:14.927
Hell, I felt most of those
things about myself today.

